nodes.bodyText:
Also what do you think about implementing a BasicAuth class to use.  So the code could change like this:
if (auth == null && user != null && !user.isEmpty()) {
    auth = new BasicAuth(user, pwd);
}
if (auth != null) {
    okHttpClientBuilder.addInterceptor(new AuthInterceptor(auth));
}
It also allows users to directly use the convenient BasicAuth class to provide basic credentials if they prefer to do that instead of the URL method.

